Package: DEMsimulation
Type: Package
Title: Simulates plausible versions of MERIT and SRTM DEMs in floodplains
Version: 0.1
Date: 2018-09-27
Authors@R: person("Laurence", "Hawker", email = "laurence.hawker@bristol.ac.uk",
  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Laurence Hawker <laurence.hawker@bristol.ac.uk>
URL: https://github.com/laurencehawker/DEMsimulation
Description: Simulate plausible versions of a MERIT DEM or SRTM DEM for floodplains based on semi-variograms. An average floodplain semi-variogram can be used or one based on landcover class.
    Alternatively, users can generate their own semi-variograms if ground truth data (usually LIDAR) is available.
License: GPL-3
LazyData: true
Depends:
  raster,
  gstat
Suggests: rasterVis, RColorBrewer,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
